-  Using Default Config File (e.g., DEV vs. DEV, all objects):
python ml_ddl_change_reporter.py (This will load default_ml_ddl_report_args.json)

- Using a Custom Config File (e.g., for DEV vs. PROD, specific FQDNs):
First, create my_custom_report_config.json:
	{
	  "source_env": "DEV",
	  "target_env": "PROD",
	  "objects": [
	    "EDP_ML_DB.ML_ALDN_PORTDB.PORTFOLIO_OPS",
	    "EDP_ML_DB.ML_ALDN_GLOBALDB.ISSUER_TICKER"
	  ],
	  "output_filename": "dev_vs_prod_critical_tables_report.md"
	}
Then run:
python ml_ddl_change_reporter.py --config_file my_custom_report_config.json



- Help:
python ml_ddl_change_reporter.py --help
